    "key_fields": [
      "process.name",
      "process.command_line",
      "process.parent.name",
      "file.path",
      "user.name"
    ],
    "notes": "Detection should focus on: (1) crontab command_line containing @reboot or non-standard schedule specifiers combined with paths under /tmp, /dev/shm, or dot-prefixed hidden files; (2) crontab -l followed rapidly by crontab - from same parent PID (enumeration then write); (3) command_line parameters suggestive of C2 (IP:port flags, -c /dev/null, &-backgrounding). Benign crontab writes are common but typically originate from /opt, /usr/local/scripts, or configuration management parents (ansible, puppet, chef). Key FP suppression: exclude parent.name in (ansible-playbook, puppet-agent, chef-client) and file paths matching /opt/* or /usr/local/*."
  },
